I am trying to perform some case discrimination for a bunch of vectors. In short, I have as input of N vectors and M clusters and I want to deduce, which cluster is closest to each vector, based on Euclidian distance. Corresponding output of this algorithm should be `device_vector&lt;size_t&gt; result` with size N and each component should be in range `[0;M)` 

What I was able to calculate so far *efficiently* is `device_vector&lt;float&gt; distances` with total size N*M, which contains distances between every vector and every cluster. That is, what I have so far has a form: `{d(v_0,c_0), d(v_0,c_1) , ..., d(v_0,c_M), d(v_1,c_0), d(v_1,c_1) ... d(v_(N-1),c_(M-2)), d(v_(N-1),c_(M-1))}` where `v_i` is ith vector, `c_j` is jth cluster vector and `d(v_i, c_j)` is the distance between the two. 

I can easily perform reduce_by_key for the key values {0,...,0 (M Times), 1, ....1, (M times), ....N,N,N,N} with binary operation less, to obtain minimal distance *value* for every vector. Than it is possible with quite a lot of additional steps to get what I want, however, this seems very inefficient, because it takes too much writes and reads from memory. 

Theoretically, from the desciption of different thrust iterators, it should be possible to make a following trick (I will describe it here schematically, for the code I am using look below):

 1. Make a zip iterator, which will zip distances.begin() with cluster number iterator [0,1,2,3...M-1, 0,1,2,3,..., M-1, ... (N times)].
 2. Write my own comparison iterator which takes as an input `thrust::tuple&lt;float, size_t&gt;`, compares with &quot;&lt;&quot; float parts provide as an output lesser tuple. Then, after all reductions are done, I will have the smallest tuple, which contains both **distance** and **cluster number**.
 3. As this output cannot be written anywhere, I also need `thrust::transform_output_iterator` which unzips the tuple and extracts `size_t` part. 

Here is the realization of that algorithm:

    //Define necessary functors and types
    typedef thrust::counting_iterator&lt; size_t &gt; countingType;  
    typedef thrust::transform_iterator&lt; UnaryFunctor_modulus_size_t, countingType, size_t &gt; modTransform;
    typedef thrust::tuple &lt; thrust::device_vector&lt; float &gt;::iterator, modTransform &gt;  tupleType;
    typedef thrust::tuple &lt; float, size_t &gt; functorTuple;
    
    struct BinaryFunctor_get_minimal_distance_tuple {   
        BinaryFunctor_get_minimal_distance_tuple(){}
        __host__ __device__
        functorTuple operator() (functorTuple partial, functorTuple x) const {
            if (thrust::get&lt;0&gt;(partial) &lt; thrust::get&lt;0&gt;(x)) {
                return partial;
            } else {
                return x; 
            }
        }
    };
    
    
    struct UnaryFunctor_get_cluster_number_from_tuple {    
        UnaryFunctor_get_cluster_number_from_tuple() {}
        __host__ __device__
        size_t operator() (functorTuple x) const {
            return thrust::get&lt;1&gt;(x);
        }
    };
    

    struct BinaryPredicate {
        BinaryPredicate(){}
        __host__ __device__ 
        bool operator() (size_t x, size_t y) const {
            return x&lt;y;
        }
    };

